19 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY Section 2, Chapter 412, O.S.L.
20 2022 (69 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 4041), is amended to read as
21 follows:
22 Section 4041. A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury
23 a revolving fund to be designated as the "Oklahoma Route 66
24 Commission Revolving Fund", which shall consist of all monies
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1571 Page 3

1 appr opriated, transferred, or otherwise designated to the fund by
2 law. The revolving fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to
3 fiscal year limitations, and shall be under the administration of
4 the Oklahoma Route 66 Commission. All monies accruing to the credit
5 of said fund are hereby appropriated, and shall be budgeted and
6 expended in accordance with the provisions of subsection B of this
7 section for the purpose of preserving and developing Route 66 and
8 commemorating the Route 66 Centennial.
9 B. No funds Funds shall be budgeted or expended from the
10 Oklahoma Route 66 Commission Revolving Fund prior to July 1, 2023,
11 or prior to the approval by the Legislature of promulgated permanent
12 in accordance with rules adopted by the Commission pursuant to the
13 provisions of the Administrative Procedures Act.
14 C. The Oklahoma Route 66 Commission shall promulgate, pursuant
15 to the provisions of the Administrative Procedures Act, permanent
16 rules subject to approval by the Legislature, to implement:
17 1. Application procedures for projects submitting requests for
18 funds;
19 2. Processes for awarding of funding applications;
20 3. Details of the Commission's general duties;
21 4. Reporting requirements of the Commission to the Legislature;
22 and
23 5. Any other rules necessary to carry out the purpose and
24 mission of the Commission as expressed in this act.
